race.comment: SPICY MISS (5) tough filly resuming. Showed a ton of grit on debut when she covered ground with a narrow second over 1100m at Rosehill in the G3 Golden Gift. Closed off well in her latest trial when second over 740m at Randwick. Stalks the tempo and gets her chance. LADY MOSCATO (6) savaged the line on debut from the wide gate with a slashing second over 1000m at the Gold Coast MM Debut. Further improved and has genuine top-three prospects. CAMPIONE D'ITALIA (2) Snitzel colt from the good producing mare Medaglia Valore on debut for the Waller yard. Impressed in all three trials and can take a hand in the finish. ESSAY (11) Zousain filly out of Written Star on debut for the Richard Collett stable. Swept down the outside in good style when second in her only trial over 799m at Warwick Farm. Respect. SATIN SUMMER (7) taken to the front on debut and proved too slick over this track and trip. Place claims best from the gate.
